    description: `Your client is a leading manufacturer in the Aluminum industry. Because Aluminum is a commodity, relative cost position is the primary source of competitive advantage, and as part of a strategic review you have been asked to construct an industry cost curve (cost/kg of aluminum produces vs. industry supply), for various plant-to-market combinations. Their are five major players in the industry, supplying six major geographic market segments. Your model should be flexible enough to enable various future scenarios to be run.`,
