    description: `The domestic semiconductor industry is beleaguered - brutal price competition from the Japanese, accusations of "dumping" against the Japanese etc. Domestic semiconductor manufacturers are clamoring for protection from Washington, and some of the public policy solutions being proposed are things like research consortia sponsored by the government, trade restraints etc. You are a consultant at a major firm. You are concerned that the public policy debate ignores basic issues regarding industry economics and whether the solutions being proposed will solve any problems for your clients. You know that each generation of memory chips lasts only 4-5 years. What are some of the factors you will consider while looking at the economics and how might they impact the idea of shared research by US manufacturers?`,
