    description: `What is the number of gas stations between New York City and Miami on I-95?`,
    solution: `No solution provided in the casebook. This is a market sizing/estimation case.`,
    evaluation: `The candidate should use a structured approach to estimate the number of gas stations. Key steps include: estimating the total distance between NYC and Miami on I-95; making assumptions about the average distance between gas stations, or the number of gas stations per mile/segment of highway; considering factors like population density, rest stops, and exits. The candidate should clearly state their assumptions and perform logical calculations.`,
