    solution: `No solution provided in the casebook. This is an M&A/valuation case.`,
    evaluation: `The candidate should outline a comprehensive valuation methodology for an insurance company. Key approaches include: discounted cash flow (DCF) analysis, considering the unique cash flow patterns of insurance (premiums, claims, investment income); comparable company analysis (multiples like P/E, P/B, EV/EBITDA for similar insurance firms); precedent transactions analysis; and embedded value (a common metric in life insurance). The candidate should also discuss qualitative factors influencing value (e.g., market position, brand, distribution channels, regulatory environment, management quality, strategic fit).`,
